    "parts": "Malleola kawakamii is a species of orchid known for its medicinal properties. Malleola kawakamii is reported to be used in traditional medicine in Taiwan, where the roots and leaves are used for their supposed health benefits. However, the specific parts of the plant used for medicinal purposes are not well-documented and may require further research. The plant is believed to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties, but more studies are needed to confirm its efficacy. Malleola kawakamii is also used in traditional medicine to treat various ailments, but the exact mechanisms and benefits are not fully understood.",
